Egypt Stocks: Ezz Steel, Orascom Telecom, South Valley Cement

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-09-21T14:10:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/egypt-stocks-ezz-steel-orascom-telecom-south-valley-cement.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
dropped for the first time in three days, decreasing 0.7 percent
to 4,433.19 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ezz Steel (ESRS)   declined for the eighth time in nine
days, losing 1.4 percent to 6.92 Egyptian pounds. Egypt’s
biggest publicly traded manufacturer of the metal was cut to
“neutral” from “overweight” and had its share-price estimate
reduced 45 percent to 8.1 pounds at AlembicHC after a court
ruling that stripped the company of two production licenses.  Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)   retreated 2.8
percent, the most in almost a week, to 3.52 pounds. North
Africa’s biggest mobile-network operator had its share-price
estimate cut to $4.7 from $5.2 by HSBC Holdings Plc. The
company’s shares trading in  London  fell 3 percent to $2.882.  South Valley Cement (SVCE)   rose to the highest level in
more than a week, advancing 2 percent to 3.65 pounds. The
company’s board of directors approved buying back 2 million
shares to support the stock price,  Al Alam Al Youm  newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
